# Deck Masters AK — 301 redirects for migration from WordPress (deckmastersak.com)
# Place this file in public/ so it is copied to dist/ for Cloudflare Pages.

/privacy-policy    /privacy    301
/privacy-policy/   /privacy    301

/category/deck     /blog       301
/category/deck/    /blog       301

/tag/deck              /blog    301
/tag/deck/             /blog    301
/tag/small-simple      /blog    301
/tag/small-simple/     /blog    301
/tag/best-decking-materials   /blog    301
/tag/best-decking-materials/  /blog    301
/tag/deck-patio-combo         /blog    301
/tag/deck-patio-combo/        /blog    301
/tag/pressure-treated-wood    /blog    301
/tag/pressure-treated-wood/   /blog    301

# Do not add `/slug/` → `/slug` for blog posts: Cloudflare Pages 308s to trailing-slash URLs for
# directory indexes, so stripping creates an infinite redirect loop for those five legacy slugs.

# (Do not add `/blog/* → /:splat`: it matches `/blog` and redirects the blog index to `/`.)

# Common WordPress / legacy paths → Astro
/about-us            /about    301
/about-us/           /about    301
/contact-us          /contact  301
/contact-us/         /contact  301

# (No self-redirects for blog slugs — e.g. `/deck-benefits` → `/deck-benefits` caused redirect
# loops with Cloudflare trailing-slash handling; `/slug/` → `/slug` is enough; see block above.)

# Legacy archive patterns seen in crawl exports
/tag/*               /blog    301
/category/*          /blog    301
/author/*            /blog    301
/gallery/homepage/   /gallery 301
